    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ceramic style, originally a folk style produced in South China, but spread to elsewhere in China, Japan, Vietnam, and many other areas of Asia; distinguished by colored glazes and low relief decoration.</Note_Text>
